{
  "texts": [
    "• Historical context stage: As the analysis continues to accumulate in the recommendation process, the agent should recommend tasks considering previous tasks and the overall goal.",
    "First, when a task is completed, the agent evaluates if the overall goal has been achieved.",
    "If not, it should recommend new tasks aligned with the goal.",
    "Second, previously unexplored tasks should be re-evaluated and proposed again if they are still relevant to the goal.",
    "Stage2: Task execution."
  ]
}